The paper deals with graph algorithms and specifically focuses on the modular decomposition tree, which is a data structure used in graph algorithms. Therefore, cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also deals with combinatorial optimization problems such as Maximum Matching and Maximum $s$-$t$ Vertex-Capacitated Flow, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) and cs.CG (Computational Geometry). The paper also mentions linear-time recognition of certain graph classes, which suggests that it could belong to cs.CC (Computational Complexity). Finally, the paper deals with graph parameters and their influence on time complexity, which suggests that it could belong to cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory).
